= Create Mesh Rest Primvar Layer =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Creates a USD layer that adds a rest position primvar to mesh primitives."""

== Overview ==

Create Mesh Rest Primvar Layer traverses all mesh primitives under the specified root and writes a rest-position primvar using the current point positions. The output is a separate USD layer that can be composited over the animation layers.

This is commonly used to provide a stable reference pose for shaders that require a rest position (e.g. for noise anchoring or displacement baking).

@parameters

Root Primitive:
    #id: root_prim
    Root of the USD hierarchy to process. All mesh descendants will receive the rest primvar.

Primvar Name:
    #id: primvar_name
    Name of the primvar to write. Default: `rest`.
